        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 2:12PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 212 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Mountain City, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mountain City and Owyhee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
